# TypeScript Rules for Next.js

## Type Definitions
- Always define interfaces for props
- Use type unions for specific values
- Prefer interfaces over types for object shapes
- Use generic types for reusable components
- Define strict types, avoid `any`

## Import/Export
- Use named exports for utilities
- Use default exports for React components
- Group imports: React, third-party, local
- Use absolute imports with path mapping

## API Types
- Define API response types
- Use discriminated unions for different response states
- Create separate types for request/response
- Use generic types for API hooks

## Component Props
```typescript
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  isVisible?: boolean;
  onAction: (id: string) => void;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
}
```

## Event Handlers
```typescript
const handleClick = (event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => {
  // handler logic
};
```

## Async Functions
```typescript
const fetchData = async (): Promise<ApiResponse> => {
  // async logic
};
```